<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/429.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Reid</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Number 334. December 2, 4 p.m. With reference to Department’s cable 2nd
                            instant re Opium Conference. British Government approves postponement.
                            Delay caused by the Foreign Office awaiting official assent of other
                            Departments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reid.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>